  "notes": "Schema v2 \u0014 refined after testing against 10 diverse nodes (1 per entity type + 1 extra). 21 novel biological context dimensions. Controlled vocabularies expanded based on real-node validation: added sulfonamide to chemical classes, pharynx/larynx/cerebellum to tissues, dendritic_spine/inner_mitochondrial_membrane to compartments, transcription_repression to molecular functions, growth_factor_signaling to pathways, metabolomic/laboratory_finding to phenotype categories, head_and_neck_neoplastic/inborn_error_of_metabolism to diseases, folate_synthesis_inhibition to mechanisms, and several others. Fields requiring external lookup (Wikidata, Wikipedia) remain optional. Highly specific or obscure entities (e.g. D-threitol plasma levels, microbial genes) are the hardest to populate \u0014 the schema accommodates them via broad categories + not_applicable terms."
}